Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Vantage Point North is a speculatively built 7.3 acre industrial and logistics site, strategically located with direct access to the M20 and M2 motorways and excellent connectivity to London and the South East markets.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Unit D, Vantage Point North, Snodland

The park is situated on the south side of the Hoo Peninsula in Medway approximately 6 miles from Rochester.

Prime site of 115 acres with the ability to accommodate over 2 million sq ft B1, B2 and B8 Industrial / Distribution opportunities, and 20 minutes from the M25 (J2).

The site benefits from fast and convenient access to the M2 motorway at Junction 1 via the duelled A228 and A289. Junction 2 of the M25 is 17 miles to the west providing access to London and the national motorway network.

Quadrant Court on Crossways Business Park is strategically located just off Junction 1A M25 (Dartford Crossing) close to Bluewater Shopping Centre and Ebbsfleet International Station.

The Channel Tunnel, Port of Dover and London Thamesport are all within easy reach via the M25, M2, and M20, while the A12 provides access to Harwich and Felixstowe.

Rail services are provided by Ebbsfleet International Station offering regular services to London St Pancras (17 mins) on the high speed line, with Greenhithe and Stone Crossing providing services to London Bridge, Cannon Street and London Charing Cross.

Crossways Business Park is a high quality landscaped business environment that has already attracted trade and logistics occupiers that include CEF, City Link, Brewers, Howdens, Screwfix, Toolstation, Eurocell and Jungheinrich at Quadrant Court with the wider Crossways estate home to Tesla, John Lewis, Yodel, Amazon, Dacher & British Gas.

Dartford X delivers a new scheme of 5 modern industrial / logistics units benefitting from easy access to the M25, Central London and the South East.

Unit sizes range from 13,025 - 72,949 sq ft.

Occupation is available from Q2 2021.
